                            <comment id="14740674" author="jira-bot" created="Fri, 11 Sep 2015 12:14:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit b3f9546196f8089cd6b7184a9a50e62affdb8a48 in qpid-jms&apos;s branch refs/heads/master from Robert Gemmell&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=qpid-jms.git;h=b3f9546&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=qpid-jms.git;h=b3f9546&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPIDJMS-108&quot; title=&quot;producers don&amp;#39;t correctly handle modified/released delivery state&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;QPIDJMS-108&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;QPIDJMS-108&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: add some tests that show the problem, disabled for now&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14740680" author="gemmellr" created="Fri, 11 Sep 2015 12:16:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added some tests showing the issue. Currently, if a rejected delivery state occurs, in the sync send case this will fail the send as expected. In the async case, it appears that the connection will be failed (prompting failover if in use) and the exception listener called as result of that (which might prompt a bit of a loop?). It may be preferable only to call the exception listener.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14740872" author="tabish121" created="Fri, 11 Sep 2015 14:11:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Don&apos;t think there was much thought put into the async send case for the error path.  Seems we should add an event point for non-fatal error that just bubble up to the connection ExceptionListener that doesn&apos;t trigger failover.  Currently the failover bit will not fail for JMSException error to allow the JMS layer to decide if the error is fatal or not. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14741252" author="jira-bot" created="Fri, 11 Sep 2015 18:00:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 7be321e7452d1e334819c1624e3d3e5d82294b47 in qpid-jms&apos;s branch refs/heads/master from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tabish121&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tabish121&quot;&gt;tabish121&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
